Subject: libperf cpumap: Ensure empty cpumap is NULL from alloc
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: dcd45b376d0ab07b987fa968a01e7a5b0c4bf837
Patch-mainline: v6.10-rc1
References: perf-sp7-v6.11-userspace-update bsc#1234698 jsc#PED-12309

Potential corner cases could cause a cpumap to be allocated with size
0, but an empty cpumap should be represented as NULL. Add a path in
perf_cpu_map__alloc() to ensure this.

